<br>
The wizard (and possibly mage, I do not know) community complained about this for well over a year, and Verant did not fix the spell.<br>
<br>
It took monks using Holgresh Beads to get the spell fixed.<br>
<br>
Monks think they got a slap in the face?  Doesn't even compare to what its like for a wizard (possibly mage as well, see above) after being ignored for an entire year only to have Verant suddenly make the requested change because of a class who can't even cast spells, much less the spell in question.<br>
<br>
Logically, the spell did need to be fixed.   On that, I am in total agreement.   However, the method to fixing the spell makes no logical sense.  It should have been fixed when it was first requested, which in fact was long before Holgresh beads ever existed.   <p><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45382><IMG SRC=http://members.shaw.ca/jlwestmoreland/sig.jpg></A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uamankhann45.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amankhann45</A> at: 2/13/02 6:00:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ukaludramaderlas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaludram Aderlas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.fortunecity.com/samslade/shadcon/Images/minisc.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 339<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/14/02 12:29:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2171.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: moo</span><hr size=1> Honestly, I am happy as peaches because now I have a non-aggro scout to do all my work.  Thanks monks! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I also think it is WONDERFUL that people who had 50-100k to blow have just lost it.  For once I love VI!  Though of course I am not entirely certain I like their newly implemented LD on zone features.   <p><img src="http://members.fortunecity.com/samslade/shadcon/Images/wizard.jpg" width="150" height="150"><BR>

